communications.subject: Washington Public Records Act Request: DV Incident
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Washington Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

1. Request any documentation relating to an investigation related to a Domestic Violence case in Lacey, WA 2022-04712, where John A. Welch (KCSO 000105578) is alleged to have committed DV against his ex-wife. Internal Affairs investigation documents relating to the case. 

2. Requesting any previous allegations from the public made against John A. Welch (KCSO 000105578).

3. All documentation relating to John A. Welch (KCSO 000105578) for reprimand, employee behavioral issues, employee performance, and any other write-ups for disciplinary issues. 

4. Any communications between John A. Welch's (KCSO 000105578) supervising officer and the Lacey Police Department regarding case# 2022-04712.

5. Any documentation relating to probation, disciplinary actions, or reprimands taken or anything under advisement.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

TIMOTHY JENKINS

communications.subject: Freedom of Information Act Request: Clandestine Intercepts - German Amateurs
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

A copy of FBI file 65-HQ-34194, on the interception of  communications made by amateur German broadcasters during World War II.

Please conduct a search of the Central Records System, including but not limited to the Electronic Surveillance (ELSUR) Indices, the Microphone Surveillance (MISUR) Indices, the Physical Surveillance (FISUR) Indices, and the Technical Surveillance (TESUR) Indices, for both main-file records and cross-reference records for all relevant names, individuals, agencies and companies. This is to include any records held at offsite locations such as the Alexandria Records Center. If any potentially responsive records have been destroyed and/or transferred to NARA, then I request copies of the destruction or transfer slips as well as any other documentation relating to, mentioning or describing said transfer or destruction, to include but not be limited to confirmation that the Bureau has no other copies of said records. If previously released records are available, then I request a rolling release consisting of those records while additional records are located and processed for release.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Paul Galante
